  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "When run `geth` with `--metrics` enable, It cannot export metrics with properly key/value tag on Ubuntu/InfluxDB. By default it should add key/value `\"host=localhost\"` for all the measurements.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `go-ethereum v1.10.15 stable`\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 20.04 (LTS) x64, InfluxDB v1.6.4\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nShould add the key value tag when export metrics to InfluxDB as below when run `SHOW TAG VALUES WITH KEY = \"host\"` query on InfluxDB\r\n\r\n```\r\n...\r\nname: geth.vflux/server/inactive/count.gauge\r\nkey  value\r\n---  -----\r\nhost localhost\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nShow nothing due to no measurements with tag key=\"host\"\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. create relevant InfluxDB database and user for `geth`\r\n2. run geth with `--metrics` enable like below\r\n```\r\ngeth --mainnet --metrics --metrics.influxdb --metrics.influxdb.database \"geth\" --metrics.influxdb.username \"geth\" --metrics.influxdb.password \"geth\"\r\n```\r\n3. using influxdb client to query the data by run below query\r\n```\r\nSHOW TAG VALUES WITH KEY = \"host\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n**N.B:** _If we run on `Debian 10 x64` then we get the expected behaviour correctly_ \r\n\r\n```\r\nname: geth.vflux/server/inactive/count.gauge\r\nkey  value\r\n---  -----\r\nhost localhost\r\n```",
